PATCH: Fix accounting report filtering by year
Adjusted the 'GenerateAccountingReport' command to correctly fetch transactions from the current year only in addition to the existing month filter. Also performed significant updates to the design and layout of the accounting report for improved user experience and clarity.

PATCH: Add EAN-13 barcode generation functionality
Implemented a new EAN-13 barcode generation based on the product ID for each product in the ShopProducts model. A new route was created to fetch this barcode. Additionally, existing ApiController methods were refactored for better readability and error handling. This enhancement will streamline product tracking and management.

PATCH: Add restricted and status fields to DeviceAuthorization
The DeviceAuthorization model has been updated to include two new properties: 'restricted' and 'status'. This will allow for more detailed and specific device authorizations, improving tracking and debugging capabilities. Error messages are now more expressive for better clarity.

PATCH: Update device restriction status in DeviceScreen
Replaced numeric values with boolean to indicate the device restriction status in DeviceScreen.php. Also, passed the device identifier through restrictDevice method in DeviceList.php for better tracking and easier debugging. For clarity, error messages in DeviceController.php are now tagged with 'error' key.

PATCH: Add new routes and methods in DeviceController
Introduced new routes for fetching orders, customers, and products in the web.php file. Additionally, expanded the DeviceController by implementing new methods: orders, customers, and products. Each method is designed to fetch required data and return them as a JSON response. Also refined the index method for a more specific return type (JsonResponse).
